        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 9:26PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 926 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Gildford to 6 miles southwest of Beaver
Creek to 6 miles east of Parker School. Movement was northeast at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Havre, Chinook, Azure, Parker School, Beaver Creek, Agency, Gildford,
Sangrey, Boneau, Hingham, Lohman, Zurich, Laredo, and Kremlin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
